author: COMSOL
description: This model illustrates how to perform eigenfrequency and frequency response analysis in a contact problem. A thin circular plate is squeezed between two smaller circular plates. The amplitude peak in a frequency response analysis is compared with the natural frequency computed from the contact state. It is also compared with the natural frequency of an ideal case, that is an annular plate clamped at the inner radius.
label: squeezed_plate_response.mph
